        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-10-22T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-10-22T13:00:00-05:00" n="139" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d139">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.00/10–2245: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gallman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-10-22T18:00:00+00:00">October 22, 1945—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 22—5:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>11050. Foreign Office official expressed gratification at Dr. Grady’s appointment
                    and said that ideas contained in Department’s 9292, October 20 seemed
                    practicable. Official remarked however that British had not selected appropriate
                    representative but matter was under active discussion and that it was hoped that
                    appointment would be made within next fortnight. Official believed however that
                    British would not be able discuss question of Greek elections with Grady “before
                    2 or 3 weeks”.</p>
                <p>Sent to Department as 11050; repeated to Paris as 679 and Athens as 71.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gallman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
